result.execSummary:
The defendant Toyoun D Mitchell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Take and Drive Vehicle w/o Consent [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(2).
  • Take and Drive Vehicle w/o Consent, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(2).
  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Attorney Katherine Graber in court with Toyoun D Mitchell. Defendant Toyoun D Mitchell in court, in custody. Attorney Michael Staskunas on behalf of Samuel E. Simpson in court for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: STW 
Case set for Sentencing Hearing. PSI received and reviewed by all parties. No additions or corrections made. Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. Additional statement made by Latoya J. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by the parties. Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of 9 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, with credit for 236 days time served. HUBER release. 

AS TO COUNT 2: The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 1 AND 4, with credit for 0 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 1 YEAR and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 1 YEAR.  

AS TO COUNT 4: The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 1 AND 2,  with credit for 0 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 1 YEAR and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEAR.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED the sentences in COUNTS 2 AND 4 and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of 3 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
The Court ordered that all court costs, fees, surcharges (including the DNA surcharge) and restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections and as a condition of probation/ extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank.
Obtain HSED or GED.
Cognitive Thinking Program. 
AS TO COUNT 2: Perform 10 hours of community service at a non-profit charitable organization.
No driving without valid license. 
Seek and maintain fulltime employment.
Restitution in the amount of $1100.00 payable to KEC. 

The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he/she may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The defendant is advised that voting rights are suspended during length of sentence.
The defendant is advised of his/her appeal rights by defense counsel.

Defendant Toyoun D Mitchell in court with attorney Katherine Graber.  Defendant Toyoun D Mitchell in custody.  Samuel E. Simpson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: STW  
Case set for Plea/sentencing hearing. Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by defense counsel and defendant.   

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT 3 dismissed and read-in to case for the purpose of sentencing.

AS TO COUNT 1, 2 and 4: Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire/Waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire and jury instruction received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Criminal Complaint/Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record. 

The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.    
Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.   

Court ordered a presentence investigation without a recommendation.  Order for presentence investigation signed and filed. 

Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into custody. Case adjourned for sentencing hearing, branch 38.
